comments: Abolished 1.10.1927 and added to the parish of Market Harborough.
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Marston Trusel.

In 1889 the part of the parish of Little Bowden in the Market 
    Harborough Urban District became part of Leicestershire, in 1894 the part remaining 
    in Northamptonshire became part of the parish of Great Oxenden, so that thereafter 
    Little Bowden was wholly in Leicestershire. Abolished 1.10.1927 and added to the parish of Market Harborough.
Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Harborough unparished area.

Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Marston 
    Trussell.
